# Implementation Phase Rules

These rules are enforced on every source file edit, regardless of which agent is active.

## Phase Gate

If `docs/arch/architecture.md` does not exist, stop immediately.
Do not write implementation code. Instruct the architect-agent to produce it first.

## Code Standards

1. Follow the API contracts defined in `docs/arch/architecture.md` exactly
2. Write unit tests alongside functional code (TDD preferred)
3. Use strict typing — no implicit `any`, no untyped Python functions
4. Follow SOLID: single responsibility, open/closed, dependency inversion
5. Document complex logic with inline comments explaining *why*, not *what*

## Definition of Done

A feature is NOT complete until:
- [ ] Compiles/transpiles without errors or warnings
- [ ] Happy-path tests pass
- [ ] Type checker passes clean
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets
- [ ] Docstrings/JSDoc on all public APIs
